com.karmant.syn

Annotation Type SynInit


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface SynInit

    Indicates that a method is an initialization method, meaning that it has to be called by SynBinder after each initialization of each object. Initialization methods are called after instantiation and binding of all objects.

    The order of invocations is undefined. If there is more than one initialization method in a single class or in a class hierarchy, all the methods are invoked for an object.
